Package io.honeycomb.beeline.tracing

Class TracerSpan

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.honeycomb.beeline.tracing.Span
      • io.honeycomb.beeline.tracing.TracerSpan
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public class TracerSpan
extends Span
    This class represents a Span that is managed by a Tracer.

    It overrides all methods of Span, and then simply delegates method invocations to the Span instance that it wraps.

    The only added functionality is in close(), which is used to notify the Tracer of the TracerSpan being closed prior to invoking close on the delegate Span. This ensures that the TracerSpan can detach itself from the Tracer context and perform any necessary cleanup.

    Thread-safety

    Instances of this class are not thread-safe. See the notes on the Tracer's javadoc for details.

      • close

        public void close​()
        Description copied from class: Span
        Closes this span in order to submit it as an Event to Honeycomb and perform any necessary clean up in the process. Overrides of Span.closeInternal() contain the logic to do this.

        The Span's duration is measured upon calling this method (as per Span.elapsedTimeMs()).

        In order to avoid clashes, because of multiple events with the same span_id being submitted, this method ensures that it is only called once and ignores multiple invocations. However, it does not use any synchronization to ensure this and is therefore not thread safe.

        This uses method allows Span to be used with try-with-resources statements.

        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
        Overrides:
        close in class Span
